le-biased infection pattern. The\n                N. allotopa\n                and\n                Ascodipteron speiserianum\n                flies, however, showed a tendency towards bats of a moderate to higher body condition, particularly reproductive females and adult males.\n              \n            \n            \n              Conclusions\n              \n                We found an overall positive correlation between parasite abundance and reproductive state and body condition of the host and female-biased parasitism for\n                M. fuliginosus\n                bats. However, the effects of body condition and female-biased infestation appear to be parasite species specific, and suggest that the mobility, life history, and potential inter-species interactions of the parasites may all play important roles.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Tai, Yik Ling", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lee, Ya-Fu", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kuo, Yen-Min", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kuo, Yu-Jen", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/1fed43208f2e3def76fcd4b37c949f5a", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/918ce33c252bdcdc54715f5b3553ee6991730ffd6e103241cbc8835617fc9fad", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/EIN27UBI", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/EIN27UBI", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/69d100f57f67aade962617cfb6a5fbad!/b133523-135810", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "s